Suddenly, I saw that i could exchange my dark squared bishop for one of my opponents knights! Furtrhermore that knight was not protected by any piece, only by a pawn. That means that after my opponent has striked back with his g-pawn, it will appear a hole in the pawn shield in the front of his king! To demolish the pawn shield in front of the enemy king is, as far as i know, a greater advantage than the bishop pair. So I gave the bishop pair up, because of this new, greater advantage. So must you think in chess.
